        <section>
          <marginalnote>Bylaws under the <actname>Park (Regional) Act</actname> prescribed</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>3</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>Bylaws made under section 4 (1) (b) of the <actname>Park (Regional) Act</actname> are a prescribed category of bylaw for the purposes of section 272 (1) (a) of the <actname>Local Government Act</actname>.</sectiontext>
          <hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 190/97.]</hnote>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Special case bylaws prescribed</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>4</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>Bylaws made by the Regional District of Okanagan-Similkameen under section 221 of the <actname>Local Government Act</actname> to regulate and prohibit the possession of opened liquor in a public place, as defined in section 1 of the <actname>Liquor Control and Licensing Act</actname>, or on a highway, are, during the period July 22, 1993 to August 9, 1993, a prescribed category of bylaw for the purposes of section 272 (1) (a) of the <actname>Local Government Act</actname>.</sectiontext>
          <hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 190/97.]</hnote>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Bylaws under the <actname>Waste Management Act</actname> prescribed</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>5</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>Bylaws made under sections 23 and 24 of the <actname>Waste Management Act</actname> are a prescribed category of bylaw for the purposes of section 272 (1) (a) of the <actname>Local Government Act</actname>.</sectiontext>
          <hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 190/97.]</hnote>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Classes of persons prescribed</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>6</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>Persons who act as</sectiontext>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>a</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>special constables, officers or members and constables of the Provincial police force or a municipal police force or members of the Royal Canadian Mounted Police,</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>b</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>clerks of municipalities,</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>c</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>secretaries of regional districts,</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>d</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>bylaw enforcement officers under section 29 of the <actname>Police Act</actname>,</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>e</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>local assistants to the fire commissioner under section 6 of the <actname>Fire Services Act</actname>, or</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>f</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>licensing inspectors, building inspectors, animal control officers or in another capacity on behalf of a municipality or regional district for the purpose of enforcement of one or more of its bylaws</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <subsandwich>are prescribed classes of persons for the purposes of section 272 (1) (b) of the <actname>Local Government Act</actname>.</subsandwich>
          <hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 190/97.]</hnote>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Ticket forms</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>7</sectionnumber>
          <subsection>
            <subsectionnumber>1</subsectionnumber>
            <subsectiontext>A ticket issued under section 272 of the <actname>Local Government Act</actname> must be in Form A or Form B.</subsectiontext>
          </subsection>
          <subsection>
            <subsectionnumber>2</subsectionnumber>
            <subsectiontext>The certificate of service and affidavit of no response to be printed on the reverse side of the ticket must be</subsectiontext>
          </subsection>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>a</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>in Form A.1 with respect to a ticket in Form A, and</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>b</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>in Form B.1 with respect to a ticket in Form B.</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <subsection>
            <subsectionnumber>3</subsectionnumber>
            <subsectiontext>The instructions to be printed on the reverse side of the copy of the ticket given to the person alleged to have contravened a bylaw must be</subsectiontext>
          </subsection>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>a</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>in Form A.2 with respect to a ticket in Form A, and</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph>
            <paragraphnumber>b</paragraphnumber>
            <paragraphtext>in Form B.2 with respect to a ticket in Form B.</paragraphtext>
          </paragraph>
          <subsection>
            <subsectionnumber>4</subsectionnumber>
            <subsectiontext>The notice of bylaw infraction must be in Form B.3.</subsectiontext>
          </subsection>
          <subsection>
            <subsectionnumber>5</subsectionnumber>
            <subsectiontext>The instructions to be printed on the reverse side of the notice of bylaw infraction must be in Form B.4</subsectiontext>
          </subsection>
          <hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 190/97.]</hnote>
        </section>
        <section>
          <marginalnote>Affidavit form</marginalnote>
          <sectionnumber>8</sectionnumber>
          <sectiontext>An affidavit in support of an application to strike out a conviction and certificate of striking out of conviction must be in Form C.</sectiontext>
          <hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 190/97.]</hnote>
        </section>
